SIMPLE: recitative
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Recitative
<hw>Rec`i*ta*tive"</hw> <pr>(r⟦ecr⟧s`⟦icr⟧*t⟦adot⟧*t⟦emac⟧v")</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It. <ets>recitativo</ets>, or F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧citatif</ets>. See <er>Recite</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A species of musical recitation in which the
words are delivered in a manner resembling that of ordinary declamation;
also, a piece of music intended for such recitation; -- opposed to
<contr>melisma</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recitative</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Recitative
<hw>Rec`i*ta*tive"</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to
recitation; intended for musical recitation or declamation; in the style
or manner of recitative.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Rec`i*ta*tive"ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recitativo</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
